The Agriculture ministry will form a new board to weed out fake veterinary officers.Livestock PS Andrew Tuimur yesterday said the Veterinary Medicines Directorate will be mandated to bring sanity to the sector. The board, in partnership with the Kenya Veterinary Board, will address challenges such as sale of fake veterinary drugs, quack vets and corruption, which is a danger to animal and human health, he said.The PS added that the ministry will also launch the Livestock and Promotion Services Board to promote livestock products and seek new markets, as well as development in arid and semi-arid areas. He spoke during the Animal Health and Industry Training Institute graduation in Kabete, where more than 104 students were awarded certificates in animal health and production, leather technology and range management courses.